According to the LED device with voltage-limiting unit and voltage-equalizing resistance of the present invention, the voltage-limiting protective unit consists one or more than more of the following units, wherein one or more than one units being in same-polarity series, parallel or series and parallel connection, which include:



    

zener diode;

varistor;

diode with property of forward voltage drop;

zener diode with property of reverse-polarity forward voltage drop

claim.claim-text:
2. An LED device, comprising:
voltage-limiting units (105) each including a semiconductor unit having a resistance that rapidly drops when subject to overvoltage;
voltage-limiting resistances (107) each including a resistive component;
at least two light-emitting units, each light-emitting unit including at least one light-emitting diode (101) in parallel with a respective one of said voltage-limiting units (105) and a respective one of said voltage-equalizing resistances (107);
at least two diodes (106);
at least two light-emitting unit sets, each said light-emitting unit diode set including at least two of said light-emitting units series or series-parallel connected to each other with a same polarity,
wherein said at least two series or series-parallel connected light-emitting units in each said light-emitting unit set is respectively parallel connected in reverse polarity with one of said diodes (106), and
wherein at least two of the light-emitting unit sets are connected in series with a reverse polarity.

4. The LED device with voltage-limiting unit and voltage-equalizing resistance as claimed in claims 1 or 2, wherein at least one said voltage-limiting unit (105) includes at least two said semiconductor units connected to each other in a same-polarity series, parallel, or series and parallel connection, said semiconductor units each including at least one of a:
zener diode;
varistor;
diode with a forward voltage drop; and
zener diode with a reverse-polarity forward voltage drop.
